description: Bust A Move 99 is part of the Bust A Move puzzle game series by Taito. Bust A Move has you shooting colored bubbles at other colored bubbles and the goal is to pop all of them on the screen. To do so you must place at least 3 of the same colored bubbles together so accuracy is the key element in this game. The trick to this game is the bubbles will keep coming down closer and closer to where your shooter is and if it falls below the shooter you lose so you must pop all the bubbles before that happens. Not only can you pop the bubbles but you can also drop them, to drop them pop higher placed bubbles above the ones you wanna drop, once you pop all the bubbles above these the lower ones will drop. Dropping bubbles is a must when playing against other players as doing so causes more bubbles to appear on there screen. The goal when playing with others or the computer is to make sure there bubbles drop under the shooting line thus causing you to win. There is also a puzzle mode where players can test there accuracy against staff made puzzles. You can play with up to 4 players and there are several characters you can choose from although some you have to unlock. This game will only save with a Controller Pak accessory so if you like the game enough make sure you have one.

title: Clay Fighter - Sculptor's Cut (USA)
description:
This is basically an expanded version of ClayFighter 63 1/3. It's got the same gameplay, same brand of humor, and the same action. So what does this game bring to the table that makes it better? Well...Â 
The game brings back some characters that got cut from 63 1/3: Lockjaw Pooch, Lady Liberty, the Zappa Yow Yow Boyz, and High Five. It has a new, less dull navigation system, and everything just looks more vibrant. The map of Claymodo Island, the character icons, even the sprites of the returning cast have been improved. The game also adds more to the story mode: pre-fight banter before the final fight, and an epilogue for you, the champ. Also added is a really catchy intro tune (Good luck gettin' it out of your head!). Basically, everything in 63 1/3 has been kicked up a notch. If you have to make a choice between 63 1/3 and Sculptor's Cut, go with Sculptor's Cut. It's just a little better.

title: International Superstar Soccer 2000 (USA) (En,Es)
description:
This is, in my humble opinion, the best soccer game to grace the face of this beautiful planet. Even newer, more shiny games pale in comparison to the pure fun you can have with it.It's soccer, so there's not much need for explanations. However, there's some things that need to be stressed. The commentary is good, easily as good as the recent games, despite this being an N64 cart. Also the crowd sounds more lively than recent games.
A small, relatively unknown quality is the 3 referees. There's the VERY lenient Hasegawa, the normal Heinz and the card-prone Carlos.
Returning from the prevous game is the player creation/renaming option so you can not only correct the goofy player names, but you can create your own team of friends/family and replace those amateurs of the world teams! There's also the scenario mode,where you can prove how well you know the game, as well as the deep, DEEP tactics and formations management options.
Also, there's a very peculiar RPG mode which plays much like a japanese visual novel, with interspersed soccer matches. Curious, to say the least. Play it, love it, worship it!

title: RR64 - Ridge Racer 64 (USA)
description:
This game, simply rocks. Everything, from the moment you turn on the game just oozes quality. Obviously this is a port of sorts of the famous PSX arcade racing series and this is the best version before the quality started going southwards.The first hing you notice about this game is the music. Oh, God, the MUSIC. It's beyond awesome, from the menu to the racing tunes and you just wait until you hear the replay theme. I literally had my hairs stand on end after playing for the first time in 10 years. Sound effects are also top-notch.
The graphics ofthis game are also excellent. Detailed cars, beautiful, crystal-clear graphics on the courses, no fog, no pop-up and a consistent and high framerate. Everything your racing game needs.
There's 10 stages in the game, unlocked gradually and then you unloock the mirror ones. Every stage you beat has a secret car you can unlock by racing against and beating it in car attack mode. There are also a few hidden cars, like the Galaga spaceship or a Pac-Man ghost.
If you like arcade racing games download it, play it, worship it! Recommended!
